<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Corporate and Investment Banking (GCIB) focuses on building long-term relationships with more than 3,000 large U.S. and multinational corporations, financial institutions and financial sponsors, by providing strong advisory expertise and capitalizing on powerful M&#38;A, corporate banking, treasury, debt and equity product expertise, to deliver integrated financial solutions.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
Summer Associates participate in an 8-10 week program, based in Asia, providing a unique opportunity and exposure to life in investment banking. In addition to learning opportunities, there are formal and social opportunities to interact and network with senior bankers.
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Summer Associates are placed directly with a specific group throughout the internship. Group placement is determined by considering business needs and the interests/skills of the Summer Associate. The groups span across country, industry and product (not all groups exist in all countries), including:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Country
	<ul>
	<li>Hong Kong</li>
	<li>Japan</li>
	<li>Singapore</li>
        </ul></li>
</ul>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Industry
	<ul>
	<li>Consumer and Retail</li>
	<li>Energy and Power</li>
	<li>Financial Institutions</li>
	<li>Healthcare</li>
	<li>Industrials</li>
	<li>Real Estate </li>
	<li>Resources</li>
	<li>Telecom, Media and Technology</li>
        </ul></li>
</ul>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Product
	<ul>
	<li>Financial Sponsors</li>
	<li>General Execution</li>
	<li>Mergers &#38; Acquisitions</li>
        </ul></li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities </H3>
<p class="bac">
Investment Banking Summer Associates play a key role in the origination and execution of work with key clients, and typically take on many of the same responsibilities as their full-time peers, including but not limited to:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working on deal teams with senior bankers and experts from other areas within the company </li>
	<li>Conducting sophisticated financial analysis and relevant industry research </li>
	<li>Participating in due diligence sessions </li>
	<li>Assisting with structuring transactions, pricing and distributing securities, and closing deals </li>
	<li>Being involved in developing new businesses, preparing and participating in client presentations, and marketing new products</li>
	<li>Assessing the impact of a transaction on a client&#39;s financial results and capital structure</li>
</ul>

